00:04:57.920 --> 00:04:58.480
Gutenberg.

00:04:59.120 --> 00:05:01.200
So, Gutenberg is moving forward.

00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:05.520
Automatic and the accessibility
team have been working for,

00:05:06.480 --> 00:05:09.920
actually, multiple years now
trying to improve and better

00:05:09.920 --> 00:05:12.080
create a usable experience.

00:05:12.080 --> 00:05:14.240
The end goals, I
can see the benefits, right?

00:05:14.240 --> 00:05:17.040
Trying to create an ecosystem
where you can create blocks,

00:05:17.040 --> 00:05:19.760
move things around, have a page
editor kind of like Wick's and

00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:20.720
aspects like that.

00:05:20.720 --> 00:05:22.040
That, you know, if
you think about it,

00:05:22.040 --> 00:05:25.760
WordPress from the beginning was
just kind of a blogging platform

00:05:25.760 --> 00:05:28.080
but now it's used to
create all kinds of websites.

00:05:29.200 --> 00:05:30.800
But execution is key, right?

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:34.400
So, of course,
needed to have an audit,

00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:35.760
needed to have part
of the practices,

00:05:35.760 --> 00:05:38.320
so Tenon.io did the
review on WP campus.

00:05:38.320 --> 00:05:40.880
I'm not gonna rehash the whole
entire history but it's a good

00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:42.960
sign that, you know, we've
gotten through two-thirds

00:05:42.960 --> 00:05:43.680
of the issues.

00:05:43.680 --> 00:05:45.680
Now, of course, UI's changed.

00:05:45.680 --> 00:05:47.120
There's gonna be
regression issues.

00:05:47.120 --> 00:05:48.560
It's an ongoing aspect.

00:05:49.440 --> 00:05:51.680
But Joe Dolson, everyone,
has been trying

00:05:51.680 --> 00:05:53.280
to really resolve this.

00:05:54.400 --> 00:05:55.760
Now, there's still
problems, right?

00:05:56.320 --> 00:05:58.800
So that's why Classic Editor's
probably one of the most popular

00:05:58.800 --> 00:06:02.240
plugins and it's because, yeah,
things like video captions,

00:06:02.240 --> 00:06:03.520
you still need it.

00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:08.160
Now, the Classic Editor plugin
should be noted that right now,

00:06:08.160 --> 00:06:10.880
it's supported only,
really, through the 2021,

00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:12.000
through the end of 2021.

00:06:12.880 --> 00:06:13.920
Now, that might change, right?

00:06:13.920 --> 00:06:16.400
Because this is really about
Gutenberg should be in a stable

00:06:16.400 --> 00:06:18.800
state, should be accessible,
should be accounting for all

00:06:18.800 --> 00:06:20.320
these things by that time.

00:06:22.080 --> 00:06:24.400
So it gets a lot of
flack but, you know,

00:06:24.400 --> 00:06:26.240
actually what about
other page builders, right?

00:06:26.240 --> 00:06:28.320
Well, why don't we use
the others ones instead of

