I miss convenience
food from Japan.

00:08:09.440 --> 00:08:12.480
And pretty much people digging
up and doing maintenance, right?

00:08:12.480 --> 00:08:13.680
'Cause it still
needs work.

00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:16.640
So I mentioned plugins.

00:08:16.640 --> 00:08:18.720
Okay, this is
probably better state, right?

00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:21.520
So if we've got page builders
creating front-end code that's

00:08:21.520 --> 00:08:26.720
having issues, maybe there's
some--one magic button

00:08:26.720 --> 00:08:27.840
that fixes everything?

00:08:29.360 --> 00:08:32.480
And so, really, I
see people submitting,

00:08:32.480 --> 00:08:34.800
people talking about it,
accessibility overlays.

00:08:34.800 --> 00:08:37.760
This has kind of become a
popular theme more recently.

00:08:39.040 --> 00:08:43.440
And so, I ask just, you know,
ask yourselves what are your

00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:45.040
expectations for this overlay?

00:08:45.040 --> 00:08:47.440
What are your expectations
in putting these plugins

00:08:47.440 --> 00:08:48.160
on your site?

00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:51.600
Because really, accessibility
should not be an afterthought.

00:08:51.600 --> 00:08:55.600
So if it's, "Hey, as developers,
we're just going to just plow

00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:58.240
ahead, keep
making code, and then,

00:08:58.240 --> 00:09:00.640
okay, well, I'll just throw in a
tool at the end that's supposed

00:09:00.640 --> 00:09:01.440
to fix everything."

00:09:03.040 --> 00:09:06.320
Well, they kind of don't
really fix everything.

00:09:07.440 --> 00:09:10.080
If you really look at it,
there's so much inside the spec

00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:11.520
that an automated tool
fixing everything

00:09:11.520 --> 00:09:13.360
is not really possible.

00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:17.680
Then you might say, "Okay, well,
it's also progressive and has

00:09:17.680 --> 00:09:20.720
been helping out people that
might need to grayscale or high

00:09:20.720 --> 00:09:24.320
contrast or, you know,
some negative contrast,

00:09:24.320 --> 00:09:25.920
some options--
right?--underlines.

00:09:27.040 --> 00:09:28.880
Now, again, if you're
making a good website,

00:09:28.880 --> 00:09:32.720
the link should already be
recognizable so why I had the

00:09:32.720 --> 00:09:33.840
link underline aspect.

00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:37.200
Increase font, decrease font,
if you've actually done a pretty

00:09:37.200 --> 00:09:40.480
decent job, it should also
already be quite large in fonts.

00:09:40.480 --> 00:09:46.320
The design era of, like, 2000s
with 9-point font aren't

00:09:46.320 --> 00:09:47.360
really there anymore.

00:09:48.400 --> 00:09:50.480
But think about it this way.

00:09:50.480 --> 00:09:54.400
So if someone with a disability
needs to have high contrast or

00:09:54.400 --> 00:09:56.720
needs to have a
certain font size,

00:09:56.720 --> 00:10:00.400
those kinds of things, they're
probably already going to have

00:10:00.400 --> 00:10:02.720
some tool, some
plugin, some software,

00:10:02.720 --> 00:10:04.640
installed on their machine
so that they can do this for

00:10:04.640 --> 00:10:06.480
every website, not
just your website.

00:10:07.120 --> 00:10:09.760
So, some of these tools end up
being a little bit redundant.

00:10:11.840 --> 00:10:15.280
Now, it's not that you really
shouldn't use it at all and

00:10:15.280 --> 00:10:16.320
there's no value.

00:10:16.320 --> 00:10:17.280
There could be some people

00:10:17.280 --> 00:10:19.360
that still somehow get
benefit from it.

00:10:19.360 --> 00:10:22.240
So that's where I kind of go,
"What are your expectations?"

00:10:23.280 --> 00:10:24.960
And there's also
some within the,

